---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — Bobbi Rose"
  description="Born and raised in Teetl'it Gwich'in territory, Bobbi Rose is a river guide, mentor, artist, and land protector based in Whitehorse, Yukon."
>
  <Header slot="header" />

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section
    class="relative pt-36 pb-20 flex flex-col justify-end overflow-hidden"
    style="min-height: 60vh;"
  >
    <!-- Hero photo background -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0" aria-hidden="true">
      <img
        src={`${base}assets/image5.jpeg`}
        alt=""
        class="w-full h-full object-cover"
        style="object-position: 50% 35%;"
        fetchpriority="high"
      />
    </div>
    <!-- Gradient overlay — bottom-heavy to protect text -->
    <div
      class="absolute inset-0"
      aria-hidden="true"
      style="background: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(15,32,39,0.30) 0%, rgba(15,32,39,0.45) 50%, rgba(15,32,39,0.82) 100%);"
    ></div>
    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <!-- Breadcrumb -->
      <nav class="mb-6" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <ol class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs" style="color: rgba(250,247,240,0.4);">
          <li><a href={base} class="hover:opacity-80 transition-opacity">Home</a></li>
          <li aria-hidden="true">/</li>
          <li style="color: var(--color-gold);">About</li>
        </ol>
      </nav>
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-4" style="color: var(--color-gold); letter-spacing: 0.2em;">About</p>
      <h1
        class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-light text-white mb-4 leading-tight"
        style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', Georgia, serif;"
      >
        Born from the Land.<br/><em class="font-light">Built on Story.</em>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-base font-light" style="color: rgba(250,247,240,0.62);">
        Teetl'it Gwich'in. Whitehorse, Yukon.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ROOTS SECTION -->
  <section class="py-20 lg:py-28 animate-on-scroll" style="background-color: var(--color-cream);">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 lg:gap-20 items-start">

        <!-- Left: Portrait photo -->
        <div class="lg:sticky lg:top-24">
          <div class="rounded-2xl overflow-hidden" style="aspect-ratio: 3/4; max-height: 560px;">
            <img
              src={`${base}assets/image0.jpeg`}
              alt="Black and white portrait of Bobbi Rose resting her chin on a carved wooden paddle with a caribou motif, wearing a beaded headband and earrings"
              class="w-full h-full object-cover"
              style="object-position: 50% 15%;"
              loading="lazy"
            />
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Right: Content -->
        <div>
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-4" style="color: var(--color-gold); letter-spacing: 0.15em;">Roots</p>
          <h2
            class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-light mb-6 leading-tight"
            style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', Georgia, serif; color: var(--color-dark);"
          >
            Teetl'it Gwich'in, Fort McPherson
          </h2>
          <div class="text-base leading-relaxed space-y-4" style="color: var(--color-mid);">
            <p>
              Bobbi Rose grew up connected to Teetl'it Gwich'in territory — the lands and waterways around Fort McPherson, NWT, known in the language as Teetl'it Zheh. Her family's relationship with the Peel River watershed, the Mackenzie Delta, and the boreal landscape runs deep, woven through generations of knowledge, language, and seasonal rhythms. That connection to place is the foundation of everything she does.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ON THE LAND -->
  <section
    class="py-20 lg:py-28 animate-on-scroll"
    style="background-color: var(--color-land);"
  >
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 lg:gap-16 items-start">
      <div>
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-4" style="color: var(--color-gold); letter-spacing: 0.15em;">On the Land</p>
        <h2
          class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-light text-white mb-8 leading-tight"
          style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', Georgia, serif;"
        >
          The River as Teacher
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-5 text-base leading-relaxed mb-10" style="color: rgba(250,247,240,0.72);">
          <p>
            Bobbi Rose came to guiding not as a profession but as a practice — a way of being in relationship with the land and water that shaped her. As a river guide with Dinjii Zhuh Adventures, she leads journeys on the rivers of Yukon and NWT that are fundamentally about more than logistics. They are about listening, about being a guest on living water, about letting place teach.
          </p>
          <p>
            Her guiding brings together Indigenous ecological knowledge, land stewardship, storytelling, and genuine hospitality. She has guided for Nahanni River Adventures and trained emerging Indigenous guides through the Arctic Inspiration Prize–supported River Guide Training Program.
          </p>
          <p>
            She is also a recognized voice in the academic and policy conversation around Indigenous land-based tourism, contributing to research on how guiding can serve both cultural continuity and ecological protection.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4">
          <a
            href="https://www.dinjiizhuh.com/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg text-sm font-semibold transition-all hover:opacity-90"
            style="background-color: var(--color-gold); color: var(--color-dark);"
          >
            Dinjii Zhuh Adventures ↗
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://nahanni.com/guide/bobbi-rose-koe/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg text-sm font-semibold transition-all hover:bg-white/10"
            style="border: 1px solid rgba(250,247,240,0.25); color: rgba(250,247,240,0.8);"
          >
            Nahanni Guide Profile ↗
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Right: On the land photo -->
      <div class="lg:sticky lg:top-24">
        <div class="rounded-2xl overflow-hidden" style="aspect-ratio: 3/4; max-height: 560px;">
          <img
            src={`${base}assets/image2.jpeg`}
            alt="Bobbi Rose among tall green riverside vegetation at a camp on the water"
            class="w-full h-full object-cover"
            style="object-position: 50% 30%;"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>
      </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TEACHING & MENTORSHIP -->
  <section class="py-20 lg:py-28 animate-on-scroll" style="background-color: var(--color-cream);">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 lg:gap-20 items-start">
        <div>
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-4" style="color: var(--color-gold); letter-spacing: 0.15em;">Teaching &amp; Mentorship</p>
          <h2
            class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-light mb-6 leading-tight"
            style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', Georgia, serif; color: var(--color-dark);"
          >
            Passing the Knowledge Forward
          </h2>
          <div class="space-y-4 text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-mid);">
            <p>
              One of Bobbi Rose's most consistent commitments is to the next generation. Through Indigenous Youth River Guide Training programs supported by the Arctic Inspiration Prize, she has helped young Gwich'in and northern youth build confidence, skills, and identity through time on the water.
            </p>
            <p>
              Her mentorship work extends beyond guiding into entrepreneurship, cultural leadership, and creative practice. She has participated in EntrepreNorth programming and continues to be a resource for youth finding their footing between cultures, between cities and land, between tradition and innovation.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 mt-8">
            <a
              href="https://arcticinspirationprize.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/River-Guide-2021.pdf"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-sm font-medium transition-opacity hover:opacity-70"
              style="color: var(--color-river);"
            >
              River Guide Training Program ↗
            </a>
            <a
              href="https://entreprenorth.ca/empowering-innovation-business-ideation-workshops/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-sm font-medium transition-opacity hover:opacity-70"
              style="color: var(--color-river);"
            >
              EntrepreNorth Workshops ↗
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Right: accent block -->
        <div
          class="rounded-2xl p-8 relative overflow-hidden"
          style="background: linear-gradient(145deg, #4A3728 0%, #1E3D4F 100%);"
        >
          <div class="absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none" style="opacity: 0.1;" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg width="100%" height="100%" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
              <defs>
                <pattern id="mentor-waves" x="0" y="0" width="120" height="40" patternUnits="userSpaceOnUse">
                  <path d="M0 20 Q30 10 60 20 Q90 30 120 20" stroke="#C4913A" stroke-width="1" fill="none"/>
                </pattern>
              </defs>
              <rect width="100%" height="100%" fill="url(#mentor-waves)"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="relative z-10">
            <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest mb-3" style="color: var(--color-gold); letter-spacing: 0.15em;">Arctic Inspiration Prize</p>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-light text-white mb-3" style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', Georgia, serif;">
              Indigenous Youth River Guide Training
            </h3>
            <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed mb-6" style="color: rgba(250,247,240,0.62);">
              A prize-supported initiative bringing young Indigenous people onto the rivers of the north, building skills, identity, and cultural connection through land-based learning.
            </p>
            <a
              href="https://arcticinspirationprize.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/River-Guide-2021.pdf"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium transition-opacity hover:opacity-80"
              style="color: var(--color-gold);"
            >
              View Program PDF ↗
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CREATIVE PRACTICE -->
  <section
    class="py-20 lg:py-28 animate-on-scroll"
    style="background: linear-gradient(160deg, #1A1614 0%, #2D2218 60%, #1E3D4F 100%);"
  >
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 lg:gap-16 items-center">
      <div class="max-w-xl">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-4" style="color: var(--color-gold); letter-spacing: 0.15em;">Creative Practice</p>
        <h2
          class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-light text-white mb-8 leading-tight"
          style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', Georgia, serif;"
        >
          Art, Fashion, and Cultural Expression
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-5 text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: rgba(250,247,240,0.68);">
          <p>
            Creativity has always been part of Bobbi Rose's practice — from beadwork rooted in Gwich'in aesthetic tradition to fashion collaborations that explore Indigenous identity in contemporary contexts. Her River Beautyyy project and collaboration with Yukon Apparel bring northern identity into wearable form.
          </p>
          <p>
            Her social presence — primarily through Instagram and TikTok as @river.beautyyy — is not just personal sharing but a deliberate act of visibility: showing what it looks like to be Gwich'in, to be from the north, to love the land and the water and also love fashion and creativity and your community.
          </p>
          <p class="text-xl font-light italic text-white" style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', Georgia, serif; color: rgba(250,247,240,0.9);">
            This is not a contradiction. It is exactly the point.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Right: Creative practice photo -->
      <div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl overflow-hidden" style="aspect-ratio: 3/4; max-height: 520px;">
          <img
            src={`${base}assets/image6.jpeg`}
            alt="Bobbi Rose kneeling in the snow wearing beaded floral mukluks, mountains and clear sky behind her"
            class="w-full h-full object-cover"
            style="object-position: 50% 20%;"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>
      </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CONTACT CTA -->
  <section class="py-16 lg:py-20 animate-on-scroll" style="background-color: var(--color-stone);">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <h2
        class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-light mb-4"
        style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', Georgia, serif; color: var(--color-dark);"
      >
        Ready to connect?
      </h2>
      <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed max-w-xl mx-auto mb-8" style="color: var(--color-mid);">
        Whether you're interested in guiding, speaking, collaboration, or mentorship — Bobbi Rose welcomes the conversation.
      </p>
      <a
        href={`${base}contact/`}
        class="inline-flex items-center px-7 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold text-sm transition-all hover:shadow-lg hover:-translate-y-0.5"
        style="background-color: var(--color-gold); color: var(--color-dark);"
      >
        Get in Touch
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer slot="footer" />
</BaseLayout>
